  "text": "Some investigators avoid possible stunning by choosing 123 I instead of 131 I for diagnostic WBS [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , Gerard & Cavalieri 2002 [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . 123 I seems more appropriate for children, as the radiation burden is smaller and the scan quality better. However, with the isotope's shorter half-life, 123 I WBS may miss a delayed uptake in distant metastases.",
